---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';

const CALENDLY = 'https://calendly.com/jt-adlard/30min';
---

<Base
  title="Atomic CFO | Fractional CFO & Decision Systems for $1M–$30M Businesses"
  description="Better decisions start with better numbers. Fractional CFO services, financial diagnostics, and decision systems for owner-led businesses doing $1M to $30M. Led by a CFA with 12 years in institutional equity research."
>
  <!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Fractional CFO for Owner-Led Businesses</p>
      <h1>
        The quality of your decisions is capped by the quality of your numbers.
      </h1>
      <p class="lede hero__lede">
        Most owners aren't short on effort or instinct. They're short on clear,
        timely, trustworthy financial information. I spent 12 years analyzing
        public companies as an institutional equity researcher. Now I bring that
        discipline to businesses doing $1M to $30M, so the big calls get made
        on evidence instead of gut feel.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__actions">
        <a href={CALENDLY} class="btn btn--gold">Book a free call →</a>
        <a href="#services" class="btn btn--ghost">How I work</a>
      </div>
      <ul class="hero__creds" aria-label="Credentials">
        <li>CFA Charterholder</li>
        <li>12 years institutional equity research</li>
        <li>Master's in Accountancy</li>
        <li>Working with owners nationwide</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WHERE DECISIONS GO WRONG ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Sound familiar?</p>
        <h2>Why good decisions are harder than they should be.</h2>
        <p class="lede" style="margin-top:18px; max-width:580px;">
          Every business I work with is run by a capable owner making hard
          calls with soft information. The patterns repeat:
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-grid">
        {[
          {
            q: 'Pricing by feel.',
            a: 'Bids and prices set on habit and competitor guesses, because nobody knows true cost by job, client, or service line.',
          },
          {
            q: 'Cash flow surprises.',
            a: 'The bank balance tells you about problems after they happen. A forecast tells you six weeks before.',
          },
          {
            q: 'Growth that hides the truth.',
            a: 'Revenue is up, everyone is busy, and you genuinely cannot tell whether you are making more money or just doing more work.',
          },
          {
            q: 'A tax accountant, but no thinking partner.',
            a: 'Your CPA keeps you compliant. Nobody is helping you decide what to do next, and the books were not built to answer that question.',
          },
        ].map((p) => (
          <div class="card reveal">
            <h3 class="pain__q">“{p.q}”</h3>
            <p class="pain__a">{p.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="reveal" style="margin-top:40px; font-size:var(--text-body); color:var(--slate);">
        None of these are character flaws. They're information problems, and
        information problems are fixable. Usually not with a big overhaul, but
        with a handful of small, precise changes in the right places. That's
        what atomic means.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ APPROACH ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--navy">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal" style="text-align:center; max-width:620px; margin:0 auto;">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Atomic approach</p>
        <h2>Small, precise moves. Compounding results.</h2>
        <p class="lede" style="margin:18px auto 0;">
          Lasting improvement doesn't come from a reorg. It comes from fixing
          the fundamentals in the right order.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps">
        {[
          {
            n: 'First',
            t: 'Get clear.',
            d: 'Clean, trustworthy numbers. Cash flow, margins, and the handful of metrics that actually drive your business, in plain English.',
          },
          {
            n: 'Then',
            t: 'Get strategic.',
            d: 'Pricing, hiring, capital, expansion. The big calls, made with evidence and a thinking partner who has analyzed hundreds of businesses.',
          },
          {
            n: 'Finally',
            t: 'Get systematic.',
            d: 'Dashboards, forecasts, and workflows that keep the clarity running without your constant attention.',
          },
        ].map((s) => (
          <div class="step reveal">
            <div class="step__n">{s.n}</div>
            <h3 class="step__t">{s.t}</h3>
            <p class="step__d">{s.d}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ SERVICES ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--cream" id="services">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
        <h2>How I work with owners.</h2>
        <p class="lede" style="margin-top:16px; max-width:560px;">
          Everything starts with numbers you can trust. From there, it's
          strategy and the systems that keep the clarity running.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Fractional CFO',
            subtitle: 'Strategic finance, without the full-time hire.',
            items: [
              'Financial strategy and planning',
              'Pricing and profitability analysis',
              'Capital allocation and budgeting',
              'Board, bank, and investor reporting',
              'Acquisition and deal analysis',
              'A thinking partner for the big calls',
            ],
          },
          {
            title: 'Financial Visibility',
            subtitle: 'Numbers you can actually run the business on.',
            items: [
              'Clean, reconciled books to build on',
              'Job costing and unit economics',
              'Margin by job, client, or service line',
              'Financial dashboards and scorecards',
              'KPI frameworks that fit your business',
              'Monthly reporting in plain English',
            ],
          },
          {
            title: 'Cash Flow & Forecasting',
            subtitle: 'See the squeeze before it arrives.',
            items: [
              '13-week cash flow forecasting',
              'Scenario planning for the big decisions',
              'Working capital management',
              'Budgeting that ties to strategy',
              'Debt and banking relationship support',
              'Integrated financial models',
            ],
          },
        ].map((svc) => (
          <div class="card reveal svc">
            <h3>{svc.title}</h3>
            <p class="svc__sub">{svc.subtitle}</p>
            <ul class="svc__list">
              {svc.items.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WHO IT'S FOR ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal" style="text-align:center; max-width:600px; margin:0 auto;">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who this is for</p>
        <h2>Businesses doing <span class="gold-text">$1M to $30M</span>.</h2>
        <p class="lede" style="margin:16px auto 0;">
          Big enough to need real financial thinking. Small enough that a
          full-time CFO doesn't make sense yet.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-grid">
        <a href="/construction/" class="who who--featured reveal">
          <div class="who__label">Contractors & Trades</div>
          <p class="who__d">
            Job costing, WIP schedules, and cash flow between draws. My deepest specialty
            has its own page.
          </p>
          <span class="who__link">Built for builders →</span>
        </a>
        {[
          { label: 'Real estate operators', d: 'Project-level cash flow and consolidated visibility.' },
          { label: 'Service businesses', d: 'Utilization, pricing, and margin by client.' },
          { label: 'Founder-led companies', d: 'A thinking partner for the owner who carries it all.' },
        ].map((t) => (
          <div class="who reveal">
            <div class="who__label">{t.label}</div>
            <p class="who__d">{t.d}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ ABOUT ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--cream" id="about">
    <div class="container about">
      <div class="about__photo reveal">
        <img src="/headshot.jpg" alt="JT Adlard, founder of Atomic CFO" width="280" height="280" loading="lazy" />
        <div class="about__name">JT Adlard, CFA</div>
        <div class="about__role">Founder, Atomic CFO · Kansas City</div>
        <div class="about__links">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jtadlard/" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="mailto:jt@atomiccfo.com">Email</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h2>I analyzed companies for a living. Now I help run them.</h2>
        <div class="about__body">
          <p>
            For 12 years I worked in institutional equity research, picking
            apart balance sheets, studying capital allocation, and figuring out
            which businesses were genuinely well run and which ones just looked
            that way from the outside.
          </p>
          <p>
            The pattern was consistent. The companies that compounded were the
            ones that understood their own numbers and had systems to act on
            them. Not smarter people. Better information, used with discipline.
          </p>
          <p>
            Atomic CFO brings that same standard to owner-led businesses. I
            don't hand you a spreadsheet and leave. I build the job costing,
            the dashboards, the forecasts, and the workflows, and I sit with
            you on the decisions that matter.
          </p>
          <p class="about__pull">
            Big transformations start with atomic-level changes in the right places.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    heading="Ready to see your business clearly?"
    body="Book a free 30-minute call. We'll look at where you are, where you want to go, and which small changes will make the biggest difference. No pitch. Just a conversation."
  />
</Base>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 110px 0 90px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff 0%, var(--offwhite) 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--warm-gray-light);
  }
  .hero h1 { max-width: 24ch; }
  .hero__lede { margin-top: 26px; max-width: 60ch; }
  .hero__actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 14px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 34px;
  }
  .hero__creds {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px 28px;
    margin-top: 44px;
    padding-top: 26px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--warm-gray-light);
    list-style: none;
  }
  .hero__creds li {
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--slate);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 9px;
  }
  .hero__creds li::before {
    content: '';
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--gold);
  }

  /* Pains */
  .pain-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 44px;
  }
  .pain__q {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .pain__a { font-size: var(--text-small); line-height: 1.7; color: var(--slate); }

  /* Steps */
  .steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    margin-top: 56px;
  }
  .step {
    padding: 36px 30px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.09);
  }
  .step__n {
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .step__t { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .step__d { font-size: var(--text-small); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Services */
  .svc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 44px;
  }
  .svc { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .svc__sub {
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold-dark);
    margin: 6px 0 20px;
  }
  .svc__list { list-style: none; flex: 1; }
  .svc__list li {
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    color: var(--slate);
    padding: 7px 0 7px 18px;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .svc__list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 16px;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--gold);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  /* Who */
  .gold-text { color: var(--gold-dark); }
  .who-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 44px;
  }
  .who {
    padding: 28px 24px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray-light);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .who--featured {
    background: var(--navy);
    border-color: var(--navy);
    transition: transform 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
  }
  .who--featured:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: var(--shadow-lift); }
  .who__label {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .who--featured .who__label { color: #fff; }
  .who__d { font-size: var(--text-small); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--slate); flex: 1; }
  .who--featured .who__d { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); }
  .who__link {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  /* About */
  .about {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .about__photo {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 36px 28px;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }
  .about__photo img {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
    border: 4px solid var(--gold);
    margin: 0 auto 18px;
  }
  .about__name { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--navy); }
  .about__role { font-size: var(--text-small); color: var(--slate-light); margin-top: 2px; }
  .about__links { display: flex; gap: 8px; justify-content: center; margin-top: 18px; }
  .about__links a {
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--slate);
  }
  .about__links a:hover { border-color: var(--navy); color: var(--navy); }
  .about__body { margin-top: 22px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
  .about__pull {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding-left: 18px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .svc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .who-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .about { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
    .about__photo { max-width: 360px; margin: 0 auto; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .pain-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .who-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero { padding: 72px 0 64px; }
  }
</style>
